Diabetic, hypertensive and even cancer patients in neighbouring countries are suffering the knock-on effect of new export regulations in South Africa. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Diabetic, hypertensive, and even cancer patients in neighbouring countries are suffering the knock-on effect of new export regulations in South Africa. On 27 March, South Africa introduced new COVID-19 Export Control Regulations. COVID-19 in SA: Test kit distribution and export delayed The new export regulations have dealt a staggering blow to medicine supplies in neighbouring countries. Michael Appel finds out how pharmaceutical companies in Namibia and Botswana are affected. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.